text: Alina Stoica (born January 18, 1979, Baia Mare) is a Romanian rhythmic gymnast. Stoica competed for Romania in the rhythmic gymnastics individual all-around competition at the 1996 Summer Olympics in Atlanta. There she tied for 11th place in the qualification and advanced to the semifinal.
